issue.title: Question: Adding additional ENA network interfaces for AWS
issue.body:
Hi, I've searched through the AWS provider module and can't find an out of the box solution to create and attach additional ENA interfaces to target VMs. Is it the case that this isn't supported out of the box and an 'network interface' resource needs to be defined on top of the existing AWS module? 

Thanks.

issue.title: AWS VM Type m3.medium not supported
issue.body:
m3.medium VM type is out of date on AWS already. Any plan to replace it with an updated one?
https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/previous-generation/

We may see the following error messages when run PKB:
WARNING VM not placed in Placement Group. VM Type m3.medium not supported
